begin_memory_text: At the beginning we talked about where we lived and how long we had been with prolific. Another thing that we discussed was how many times we have had this chat before
middle_memory_text: We talked about how he got into prolific and REV. He found it on a reddit or a subreddit named Beermoney. Then he told me about his experience with Swagbucks.
end_memory_text: The corona virus, how you take your own life in your hands when you go outside, he wears a mask and hasn't had a haircut since March
rest_of_day_open: I have dinner tonight with my husband, then we will watch TV. I have a phone interveiw tomorrow before noon. Then I will read another book, complete some cross stitch that I have been working on, go to the grocery store, do some cleaning around the house and look for work.
critical_positive: What worked well was that he was a native English speaker. He seemed intelligent when he said that he was a freelance programmer. He talked about REV and about reddit, I liked that he had been on prolific for over a year and liked that he could make some decent money on that.
critical_negative: I think he was a bit pre occupied with his hair. he kept messing with his hair, I also felt that I was like 2 steps ahead of him with the conversation...like I knew where the conversation was going to go and I was waiting for him to catch up to me.

begin_memory_text: We asked eachother where we were from and how many of these video chats we'd done before. Turns out this was number five for both of us.
middle_memory_text: We talked about various ways of making money online. She's got a lot more going on than I do. I'm thinking about looking into stocks, although there's probably a lot I should learn before I start buying.
end_memory_text: Dealing with covid in our respective states. She's in Florida so things have been pretty scary down there, I live in Oregon and our numbers haven't been too bad so far.
rest_of_day_open: Not bad. I'll probably mostly stay in, although I have to go out for groceries at some point. I'll code, do some cooking, probably read a book or two. I have a doctor appointment Wednesday but I can do that via phone. With covid and all every week tends to look about the same writ large.
critical_positive: We had a fairly easy rapport, I think. After the usual starting awkwardness the conversation pretty much just kept going. We talked a lot about making money online, and she's been at it longer than me so she gave me a lot to think about. It was just a smooth conversation.
critical_negative: There wasn't really much that went badly. She did mention getting a guy once who was on a VPN and refused to give many details about himself, which seems like it would make it hard to have a conversation, but we didn't have any issues like that with eachother and I've yet to encounter someone like that.
